\date{2026-03-30}
\title{Universal property of modal equivalences and connected maps}
\author{fredrikbakke}
\meta{external}{https://github.com/samtoth/agda-synthetic-categories/pull/71}
\tag{changelog}
\import{stt-macros}

\subtree{\title{Summary}
\p{
We formalise a series of characterisations and basic properties of
[connected maps](Modalities.ConnectedMaps) and
[modal equivalences](Modalities.ModalEquivalences), most notably, the following
characterisation theorem of connected maps.
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Characterisation of #{K}-connected maps}
\taxon{Theorem}

\p{
Given a [(global) subuniverse](Modalities.GlobalSubuniverses) #{K} and a map
#{f : A \to B} whose [fibres](stt-000M) have #{K}-[reflections](stt-007B)
#{\eta_{(-)} : \prod_{(b:B)}{\fibre{f}{b}\to K\fibre{f}{b}}}, then the following
conditions are equivalent:

\ol{
\li{The map #{f} satisfies the [universal property of #{K}-connected maps](fre-LMAB):
for every #{K}-valued family #{U} over #{B}, the following dependent precomposition
map is an equivalence ##{\Pi_f U : (\prod_{b:B}{U(b)}) \to (\prod_{a:A}{U(f(a))}).}}
\li{For every #{K}-valued family #{U} over #{B}, every section
#{u : \prod_{a:A}{U(f(a))}} uniquely extends along #{f}.}
\li{The map #{f} is left orthogonal to all #{K}-maps.}
\li{The fibres of #{f} are #{K}-equivalent to contractible types.}
\li{The constant map #{{\Delta} : U \to (\fibre{f}{b} \to U)} is an equivalence for
every #{b:B} and every #{U} in #{K}.}
\li{For every #{K}-valued family #{U} over #{B}, #{\Pi_f U} is surjective.}
\li{For every #{b : B} the following type is (merely) inhabited
##{\sum_{(u:K\fibre{f}(b))}{\left(\prod_{(a,p):\fibre{f}(b)}{u =_p^{K\fibre{f}{}}\eta_{f(a)}(a,{\refl})}\right)}.}}
}
Moreover, even if the fibres of #{f} are not assumed to have #{K}-reflections,
conditions 1--3 are equivalent, and 4--5 are equivalent, and the latter imply the
former, while [the converse fails in general](fre-00EM).
}
}

